You can use the continue statement in for, select, and while loops. For more information about other loop statements, see:
- Endloop Statement
- For Statement
- Select Statement
- While Statement

### Parameters--Continue Statement
This statement has the following parameter:
#### label
Specifies which loop to continue using in an Actian 4GL OpenROAD Continue Statement. This must be a character string without quotation marks and cannot be a keyword (see 4GL Keywords). If you do not specify a value for a label, OpenROAD continues with the innermost loop.

### Examples--Continue Statement
Process all changed rows:
```
i = 1;
while i <= x.LastRow do
     if x[i]._RowState != RS_CHANGED then
          i = i + 1;
          continue;
     endif;
     /* Process row */
     i = i + 1;
endwhile;
```
